symbol.title: Chinese knot - a traditional decrotive handicraft. The most typical knots are made of red threads.

Traditional Chinese coin - this type of coin with circular edges and rectangular holes in the middle dates back to the earliest Chinese dynasties. Nowadays, it serves decrotive purposes during festivals and celebrations.

Handheld fan - as its name suggests, this fan is held and waved by hand to create air flow and make you feel cooler. It was widely used in China before the dawn of ACs. Today the fan still has both practical and aesthetic uses in China.

Firecracker - usually used by families during the Spring Festival. The "formal" purpose of the firecracker is to break away from the old year and celebrate the new. Children also play with it for fun.

Chinese dumpling, Baozi and Tangyuan - very typical Spring Festival foods in China. During the whole festival period, every household cook these meals; if dining out, basically everyone would order them.

Chinese red lantern - another popular decorative art piece during the New Year celebrations. Nowadays people don't usually make them by hand anymore; but you could see manufactured lanterns hanging in many places.

Red Pocket - Chinese children's favorite. The Red Pocket is a red envelop containing money, given to children in the family by the elders. Today, we also have the digital (mobile) version of red pocket in popular social media applications like WeChat.
